Stereotype.notes:
The HTML is built using contentBefore + contentBody(1st row) + contentSeparator + contentBody(2nd row) + ... + contentBody(last row) + contentAfter. Expression available in contentBody: {column-name} is replaced with the value in that column of the row being processed. {anything except a column-name} is executed as a javascript expression. You may use {'column-name} inside. oThis in expressions reffers to the HTMLBrowse object (you can use oThis._objectName or oThis.getObjectName() and so on).

E.g. :
{item-name}, {{on-hand} < 1 ? "Out of stock" : ""}
